President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key positions in his Administration. Robert Joseph Kruckemeyer of Texas has been nominated to be a Member of the National Council on the Humanities. Mitchell A. Silk of New York has been nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of the Treasury for International Markets and Development. Peter J. Coniglio of Virginia has been nominated to be the Inspector General of the Export-Import Bank of the United States. Additionally, President Trump has announced his intent to appoint Joseph Preston of Massachusetts to be a Member of the Advisory Committee for Trade Policy and Negotiations, and several individuals to be Members of the United States Commission for the Preservation of America's Heritage Abroad.